He saw a troubling theme in mathematics instruction: a serious disconnect between the students' basic skills training and the curriculum they were expected to master in the years to come. They weren't being prepared properly for their future.Larry set out on a mission: to find an approach that would provide children with the strong foundation they needed to succeed. Over the next three decades, he painstakingly developed and assembled a blend of methods and materials. Description: We make math make sense! As a math learning center for helping kids in grades 2-12 our instructional approach goes beyond traditional math tutoring in order to develop understanding …Learn more about Mathnasium of El Segundo, Opens a popupSpecialtiesWe make math make sense! As a math learning center for helping kids in grades 2-12 our instructional approach goes beyond traditional math tutoring in order to develop understanding and build a love for math. When math makes sense, kids leap way ahead in math. The Mathnasium Method™ transforms the way kids learn math.Mathnasium students start by taking a customized assessment which pinpoints their learning needs. Next, we design a customized learning plan for teaching the concepts the student needs to master. Our specially trained math instructors will work with your child to understand math in an individual setting. We meet them where they are and take them where they need to go. Assessments continue throughout your student's Mathnasium instruction to ensure that your child retains the skills they've learned.Our math tutors also will set aside time to provide homework help. We help kids understand the homework assignment so they feel better prepared to complete the work at home.Offering math tutoring and homework help, our math specialists are passionate about helping kids improve and excel in math through our year-round as well as summer math programs. Our math learning center is located in El Segundo at the corner of Sepulveda and Mariposa, across from the Ralphs supermarket and the Hacienda Hotel. We also serve students from neighboring communities including Westchester, Playa Vista, Playa del Rey, Inglewood, Hawthorne, Lawndale, Manhattan Beach, and the South BayHistoryEstablished in 2014.Mathnasium is an international chain of year-round math learning centers where children go to improve their math skills. Each franchised center utilizes the Mathnasium Method, an individually customizable educational curriculum created through over 35 years of classroom experience and research. The goal is to teach kids math in a way that makes sense to them.Regardless of your child's future career choices, it is important to have a solid understanding of mathematical concepts beyond mere memorization of formulas and procedures. These basic mathematical concepts along with problem solving skills are the key building blocks to success in all walks of life.We are located in El Segundo, and we also serve students from neighboring communities including Westchester, Playa Vista, Playa del Rey, Inglewood, Hawthorne, Lawndale, Manhattan Beach, and the South Bay.Meet the Business Owner

Description: We know how to teach your child math. Our specially trained math instructors will teach your child how to understand math in an individual setting - our unique approach enables us …Learn more about Mathnasium of Studio City, Opens a popupSpecialtiesWe know how to teach your child math. Our specially trained math instructors will teach your child how to understand math in an individual setting - our unique approach enables us to effectively explain math concepts well and lend a helping hand to every student. Our tutors foster a caring, encouraging environment that helps kids thrive and learn! We pinpoint your child's learning needs, meet them where they are, and take them where they need to go.Mathnasium instructors use our unique assessment process to determine (with great accuracy) exactly what each child knows and what they need to learn. Next, we design a customized learning plan for teaching the concepts the student needs to master. It doesn't stop there - our encouraging instructors continually check progress along the way to make sure kids truly understand and retain the concepts we've taught. The results are transformative - kids will see measurable changes in attitude, confidence, and school progress. We will help your child overcome homework frustration.Our instructors will also set aside time to provide homework help. We help kids understand the homework assignment so they feel better prepared to complete the work at home - underscoring their understanding of concepts and transforming homework frustration into a welcome challenge.HistoryEstablished in 2015.Mathnasium Learning Centers strive to teach elementary, middle, and high school students math the way that makes sense to them. The hallmark of our program has been the way that it engages kids and gets them to know math at a level that is far beyond adult expectations. Today, over 35 years after its inception, the Mathnasium Method(tm) is providing children all over the world with the confidence, critical thinking skills, and mathematical ability to last a lifetime. We specialize in math tutoring, customer learning plans, personalized instruction, homework help, and SAT, ACT, and ISEE preparation. Our goal is to significantly increase your child's math skills, understanding of math concepts, and overall school performance, while building confidence and forging a positive attitude toward the subject. Find out what the bar Graders are Looking for. Great Bar Pass Rates.Open Book Bar Prep is an innovative California Bar Exam prep course. The fundamental philosophy is to understand what the bar graders need and speak the "bar language" through comprehensive one-on-one instruction.The California Bar Exam does not test on memory retention, but on application. Bar graders look for students to apply the law on a case by case basis. Our course focuses on all three sections of the bar exam: Performance, MBEs and Essays. Every area of study is reviewed one-on-one with our teaching staff. Students also gain access to the Learning Center, which is equipped with personal workspace, Wi-Fi, library and kitchen.We show students how to organize, categorize, and apply laws and facts. By helping students master skills, such as dialoguing about a given scenario and using the law to support the conclusion, we provide you with the toolHistoryEstablished in 2006.The bar exam measures a student's ability to represent clients, not to represent the law. The Open Book Bar Prep course is founded on personal attention. We believe that the key to a student's success is one-on-one tutoring, dialogue, and practice. The Learning Center was created to give students a comfortable place to study. Full-time students obtain 24/7 entry to the Learning Center, which includes personal space, Wi-Fi, access to a library, and use of a kitchen. Open Book Bar Prep began shortly after the founder graduated from law school. The founder saw the bar exam in a different light than most: he enjoyed it! He then helped several of his friends pass the bar exam and soon after, attracted students and clients with his unique perspective and company strategies of the bar.Meet the Business Owner

We take input from the people that know the student best (you and the student's teacher), and merge these ideas with the standards that the nation expects all students to master at that grade level." Our program creates tailored, individualized lesson plans that help …Learn more about The Learning Path - Temp. CLOSED, Opens a popupSpecialtiesWelcome to The Learning Path! The Learning Path helps students excel in Math, Reading, Writing, and in Life. Our program creates tailored, individualized lesson plans that help students master the fundamentals for learning anything, teaching children to teach themselves, and giving students a joy for learning. Our program creates confident, capable, and independent students. Our students range in age from preschool, starting at 3 years of age and learning how to read, and extend all the way to high school, with students preparing for the SAT and mastering higher level Math. Our diagnostic testing and curricula are mapped to the new Common Core standards. For younger students, we emphasize a mastery of fundamental skills in the basics before shifting focus to the Common Core. We have extensive and proven experience helping children, having been in business since 2009. We have transformed countless students from struggling in school to being at the top of their class.HistoryEstablished in 2009.We have gone through a couple of name and curricula changes over the last few years, all in an effort to find the most effective programs for our children. It is our job to ensure that we are having the maximum effect on a child's education, but in a way that engages the student and makes them excited to learn. We do not believe in a one size fits all approach.The Learning Path employs people who are excited and happy to work with children, who are leading examples within the community. For instance we have employed high school seniors from public Magnet schools that have gone on to MIT and Notre Dame, to name only two.
